s specific to acute hepatitis B infection.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044988,0.082361,0.093929,0.099642,0.10211,0.099526,0.098755,0.0908,0.082395,0.079563,0.067323,0.058606],"unified_progress":[0.048301,0.072761,0.0912,0.097141,0.10251,0.10383,0.10141,0.093769,0.087459,0.07995,0.067628,0.054041]},{"section":9,"text":"HBeAg is the e-antigen, which typically indicates high viral replication and infectivity.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040239,0.077826,0.089373,0.097431,0.10121,0.10078,0.10049,0.093665,0.085147,0.083892,0.069865,0.060081],"unified_progress":[0.043712,0.069075,0.086972,0.096303,0.10166,0.10604,0.10429,0.096937,0.090107,0.08283,0.068878,0.053193]},{"section":10,"text":"Putting this together: the presence of HBsAg and IgM anti-HBc together is classic for acute hepatitis B.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.047866,0.083194,0.091718,0.095841,0.095305,0.092128,0.091895,0.087937,0.083233,0.083755,0.074653,0.072474],"unified_progress":[0.056411,0.068653,0.081083,0.09057,0.095186,0.096634,0.096986,0.093411,0.089425,0.085806,0.078113,0.067721]},{"section":11,"text":"The high transaminases and jaundice fit with acute liver inflammation.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034961,0.071419,0.083374,0.089991,0.094142,0.095579,0.097958,0.094763,0.091601,0.088788,0.083288,0.074136],"unified_progress":[0.045619,0.063324,0.075163,0.082311,0.090118,0.095643,0.096602,0.096717,0.096546,0.095514,0.088975,0.07347]},{"section":12,"text":"The HBeAg positive suggests it's in the active, replicative phase, which is common in acute cases.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037188,0.073072,0.083456,0.09037,0.094378,0.096251,0.097152,0.094378,0.090262,0.088956,0.079908,0.074629],"unified_progress":[0.043648,0.065227,0.077657,0.085066,0.091431,0.096323,0.097594,0.096553,0.094891,0.09251,0.085186,0.073916]},{"sec